The Group Chief Executive Officer of the Nigerian National Petroleum Company Limited (NNPC Ltd), Mallam Mele Kyari, on Thursday visited President Bola Tinubu at his residence in Lagos, in the spirit of the Eid-El-Kabir celebration. Kyari, who stated this in a post on his Twitter page, said he visited the President with the Acting Governor of the Central Bank of Nigeria, Mr. Folashodun Shonubi. The NNPC boss expressed joy for the privilege to pay the homage to the President, adding that Sallah is a day of reaffirmation by the faithfuls to sacrifice or give off the most coveted of possessions to please Allah. He wrote, “Privileged to pay Sallah homage to Mr President alongside Ag. Gov CBN. A day of reaffirmation by the faithfuls to sacrifice or give off the most coveted of possessions to please Allah and by implication for the common good… and to ultimately be grateful for all the favours of Allah and secure the infinite mercy of Allah. Eid Mubarak.”